# Module

::READ (Construct: Tag) FROM `../expressions/tag.art`.
::READ (Construct: NaturalName) FROM `../expressions/natural-name.art`.
::READ (Construct: NaturalBlock) FROM `./natural-block.art`.

## Construct: SectionBlock

**Category:** Structural

**Purpose:** Represent a named structural section of a document.

**Description:** A SectionBlock is a structural construct consisting of a heading and its associated content. A SectionBlock MAY define an optional type, a name, tags, and arbitrary content. The interpretation of the content is determined by the enclosing grammar or construct.

<!-- refine content rules -->

**Schema:**

```
SectionBlock {
    type?: <NaturalName>
    name: <NaturalName>
    tags?: <Tag>[]
    content: <NaturalBlock>
}
```

**Syntax:**

```art
<syntax-block-header> =
    ### [<NaturalName (section-block.type)>: ]<NaturalName (section-block.name)>

<SectionBlock> =
    <syntax-block-header> <Tag> [<Tag> ...]
    <NaturalBlock>
```

**Rules:**

- A SectionBlock MUST define a name.
- A SectionBlock MAY define a type.
- A SectionBlock MAY be tagged with one or more Tag.
- A SectionBlock MAY contain arbitrary content.

**Examples:**

Example of Section Block without type.

```md
## Rules

Lorem ipsum
```

Example of Section Block with type `rule`.

```md
### Rule: Maximum 4 items

This is a rule.
```

Example of Section Block with tags.

```md
### Routine: List Tasks (#producer) (#wip)

**Purpose:** List tasks according to criteria, ...
```
